==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: del
<hw>del</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Math.)</fld> <def>a differential
operator which, operating on a function of several variables, gives the
sum of the partial derivatives of the function with respect to the three
orthogonal spatial coordinates; -- also called the
<altname>gradient</altname> or <altname>grad</altname>. It is
represented by an inverted Greek capital delta (⟦nabla⟧), and is thus
because of its shape also called <altname>nabla</altname>, meaning
<it>harp</it> in Hebrew.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Delaceration</ent>⟦br⟧
